  "verdict_text": "C \u00d7 F2_vector at n_max=3 = 1.4754e-02 is far from alpha/(2*pi) = 1.1614e-03 (ratio = 12.7039). Vector promotion does NOT close the C \u00d7 F2 negative result. Structural reason: the vector vertex enforces selection rules (GS structural zero, m_j conservation, etc.) but does NOT self-consistently match the projection constant C, which was derived from the SCALAR graph-VP vs continuum-VP ratio. The continuum F2 = alpha/(2*pi) requires both the vector vertex AND the alpha-dependent coupling at the action level, which is the calibration tier (Paper 18) that lives outside the graph."
